: "public", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 1, "created_at": "2022-08-10T23:26:51Z", "updated_at": "2022-08-11T20:05:15Z", "closed_at": "2022-08-11T20:05:04Z", "author_association": "NONE", "type": null, "active_lock_reason": null, "draft": false, "pull_request": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pimalaya/himalaya/pulls/404", "html_url": "https://github.com/pimalaya/himalaya/pull/404", "diff_url": "https://github.com/pimalaya/himalaya/pull/404.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/pimalaya/himalaya/pull/404.patch", "merged_at": "2022-08-11T20:05:04Z"}, "body": "Updated himalaya#msg#write:\r\n  - New buffer opens in split view (mirrors behavior of opening a\r\n    message from the mailbox list view)\r\n  - Function accepts an optional argument for populating the buffer with\r\n    existing content, rather than relying on the default msg template\r\n    (see updated \"cancel\" behavior below)\r\n\r\nUpdated himalaya#msg#draft_handle:\r\n  - \"c\" option (to cancel exiting the new message buffer) now passes the\r\n    existing buffer content back to himalaya#msg#write. This is because\r\n    Vim does not allow event interruption. Without the ability to stop\r\n    the buffer closing event, message content will be lost unless\r\n    preserved and reinserted. With these changes, the \"c\" option now\r\n    seems -- for the user -- as if the request to close the buffer was\r\n    truly cancelled.", "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pimalaya/himalaya/issues/404/reactions", "total_count": 1, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 1, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pimalaya/himalaya/issues/404/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null, "score": 1.0}]